//*************************************************************
//********************PREDICTION BLOCK *************************
//************************************************************
Optional: make your analogue prediction scale display 1–1000 (same trial, block-controlled)

Right now you hardcode:

/ lastresponsedisplayed = round(values.lastresponse/1000)

If you replace it with a scale-aware version, you can switch between “0–10” and “0–1000” just by changing values.scalemaxdisplayed (and your anchors already use <%values.scalemaxdisplayed%>):

/ displaydivisor = values.scalemax / values.scalemaxdisplayed
/ lastresponsedisplayed = round(values.lastresponse / expressions.displaydivisor)

Then, in any “high granularity prediction” block you can do:

/ onblockbegin = [values.scalemaxdisplayed = 1000]


/ displaydivisor = values.scalemax / values.scalemaxdisplayed
/ lastresponsedisplayed = round(values.lastresponse / expressions.displaydivisor)

/ onblockbegin = [values.scalemaxdisplayed = 1000]


